-- Apple IPhone Users Have U.S. Blessing to `Jailbreak,' Add Own Applications
-- Todd Shields
-- 2010-07-26T15:30:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/-jailbreaking-of-mobile-phones-to-add-apps-backed-by-library-of-congress.html

          
          
             Owners of Apple Inc.’s iPhone can
unlock the device in order to use applications not authorized by
the company, the U.S. Library of Congress said today.  
 The decision on “jailbreaking” of iPhones and other
smartphones was posted on the agency’s website.  
